alone was $US36 992/QALY in the base-case analysis (2007 values). The 
sensitivity analysis showed the highest net benefit for radiotherapy alone if 
the cost of cetuximab increased by 50%.
CONCLUSION: This study demonstrated that the addition of cetuximab to high-dose 
radiotherapy regimens is likely to be cost effective in Taiwan because the 
incremental cost per QALY is below the commonly accepted cost-effectiveness 
